## Common Mistakes

- Accepting AI suggestions without reviewing the code logic for correctness and security vulnerabilities
- Using vague or ambiguous prompts that result in generic, incorrect, or irrelevant code
- Over-relying on AI for complex business logic that requires deep domain knowledge and understanding
- Not providing sufficient context about the project framework, coding style, or existing patterns
- Assuming generated tests provide complete coverage without manually identifying edge cases specific to your domain
- Failing to verify that AI-generated code follows your project's naming conventions and architectural patterns
- Accepting the first generated output without iterating on the prompt for better results
- Using outdated or deprecated API calls in generated code without updating them
- Generating code with hardcoded values or magic numbers instead of configurable constants
- Not reviewing AI-generated documentation for accuracy and completeness


## Best Practices

- Always review every AI-generated code snippet before accepting it, treating it as a first draft that requires expert validation
- Provide explicit context in prompts including language version, framework, and project conventions to ensure relevant output
- Use iterative prompting—start with a simple request and refine based on initial results rather than writing elaborate prompts upfront
- Split complex tasks into smaller, focused prompts to generate more accurate and manageable code sections
- Combine AI assistance with static analysis tools and linters to catch issues that the AI might miss
- Maintain a personal prompt library of effective prompts that work well for your common development tasks
- Test AI-generated code thoroughly before integrating, especially for security-sensitive operations and edge cases
- Use AI for boilerplate and patterns, but apply your expertise for business logic and architectural decisions
- Document your AI interactions and outcomes to build institutional knowledge about effective AI usage in your team
- Stay updated on your AI plugin's capabilities and limitations through changelogs and community best practices

